WEBVTT

00:00:32.915 --> 00:00:33.756
Monday morning,

00:00:33.795 --> 00:00:37.036
we're back in the library studio.

00:00:37.216 --> 00:00:38.457
I am your host, Craig Winn.

00:00:38.496 --> 00:00:42.118
We're going to continue our series where

00:00:42.658 --> 00:00:45.558
we're trying to understand the picture

00:00:45.579 --> 00:00:48.518
that was painted in the last Mashal.

00:00:48.738 --> 00:00:51.420
It is Proverbs thirty one,

00:00:51.799 --> 00:00:56.180
and it was remarkable and that it is

00:00:56.280 --> 00:00:56.621
about

00:00:57.521 --> 00:01:00.503
Our King, the Messiah, the Chosen One,

00:01:00.863 --> 00:01:03.987
the man who ultimately became our Savior

00:01:04.027 --> 00:01:05.507
by fulfilling Pesach, Matsah,

00:01:05.567 --> 00:01:06.688
and Bikuwrym in the year of the

00:01:06.709 --> 00:01:07.590
Thirty-Three C.E.

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:10.852
The very man that was counterfeited to

00:01:11.373 --> 00:01:13.114
create the myth of Jesus.

00:01:15.093 --> 00:01:17.715
he had a really low moment in his

00:01:17.795 --> 00:01:20.016
life, and so he needed an intervention.

00:01:20.615 --> 00:01:20.995
Yes,

00:01:21.697 --> 00:01:23.938
it is true that the Son of God

00:01:23.957 --> 00:01:26.358
and the Messiah was a really bad boy.

00:01:27.299 --> 00:01:30.221
He, in his pursuit of Bathsheba,

00:01:31.141 --> 00:01:34.183
not only took a married woman's life,

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:37.290
to be his and impregnated her.

00:01:38.292 --> 00:01:41.552
But then he schemed to kill her husband

00:01:41.591 --> 00:01:42.572
so that he could keep her.

00:01:43.653 --> 00:01:46.513
And God did not like that one little

00:01:46.673 --> 00:01:50.274
bit and dressed him down and they

00:01:50.373 --> 00:01:53.174
engendered a serious timeout for bad

00:01:53.215 --> 00:01:53.694
behavior.

00:01:54.715 --> 00:01:58.695
And it was during that period that our

00:01:58.715 --> 00:02:01.596
King who, well,

00:02:01.637 --> 00:02:02.816
in the Psalm that he

00:02:04.102 --> 00:02:06.703
revealed after God's dressing down,

00:02:06.742 --> 00:02:10.604
where God said what you did was a

00:02:10.664 --> 00:02:14.325
total rejection of who I am and my

00:02:14.445 --> 00:02:16.766
testimony to you, my instructions to you.

00:02:17.627 --> 00:02:19.068
And as a result of this,

00:02:20.968 --> 00:02:22.310
really horrid things are going to happen

00:02:22.349 --> 00:02:23.590
to you and to Israel.

00:02:24.189 --> 00:02:25.411
You know, I cannot overlook this.

00:02:25.431 --> 00:02:29.733
And so after everything did fall apart,

00:02:31.171 --> 00:02:34.235
Had his daughter raped by his son.

00:02:34.717 --> 00:02:36.520
Then one son killed another son.

00:02:36.580 --> 00:02:38.742
And then that son led a coup against

00:02:38.802 --> 00:02:38.984
him.

00:02:39.063 --> 00:02:42.269
I mean, it was horrid what happened.

00:02:43.751 --> 00:02:45.312
But he then had an intervention.

00:02:46.461 --> 00:02:48.462
And that intervention came by way of

00:02:48.543 --> 00:02:49.443
Yahowah's Amah.

00:02:49.984 --> 00:02:52.284
Yahowah's Amah is a character that is

00:02:52.365 --> 00:02:54.765
portrayed throughout the story.

00:02:55.105 --> 00:02:57.206
She makes a number of appearances and

00:02:57.227 --> 00:03:00.048
she's spoken of quite frequently

00:03:00.127 --> 00:03:00.927
prophetically.

00:03:01.808 --> 00:03:05.129
She could even be the voice of many

00:03:05.349 --> 00:03:06.991
of the Mashal word pictures,

00:03:07.471 --> 00:03:10.612
could in fact be she and her husband

00:03:11.453 --> 00:03:12.954
talking to their son,

00:03:13.014 --> 00:03:15.675
giving their son advice about Yahowah.

00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:19.397
and his participation in the Covenant

00:03:19.419 --> 00:03:19.859
family.

00:03:21.920 --> 00:03:27.187
And her interaction with Dowd is the

00:03:27.247 --> 00:03:28.968
subject of the final

00:03:29.491 --> 00:03:30.110
word picture,

00:03:30.450 --> 00:03:32.072
which is the basis of this series.

00:03:32.111 --> 00:03:33.473
And we've gone over it in previous

00:03:33.513 --> 00:03:34.032
programs.

00:03:34.592 --> 00:03:36.193
And it's rather astonishing.

00:03:36.294 --> 00:03:38.215
And it establishes this Amah,

00:03:38.634 --> 00:03:42.757
this surrogate mother, this Amah of Dowd,

00:03:42.796 --> 00:03:46.557
who is referred to as Ashar.

00:03:47.519 --> 00:03:50.060
And Ashar

00:03:51.092 --> 00:03:54.615
goes back to the days of Leah when

00:03:54.735 --> 00:03:59.079
she gave birth to the tribe of Asher,

00:03:59.118 --> 00:04:00.860
the first born of Asher,

00:04:01.641 --> 00:04:03.883
and said that she would be remembered

00:04:03.943 --> 00:04:06.566
forevermore as Ashar.

00:04:07.426 --> 00:04:10.088
And then Dowd goes so far as to

00:04:10.129 --> 00:04:13.652
say that this is the most extraordinary of

00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:16.115
all women who have ever lived.

00:04:16.134 --> 00:04:16.875
There are a number of other

00:04:18.607 --> 00:04:24.932
Mashal and Mizmowr, Proverbs and Psalms,

00:04:25.492 --> 00:04:26.434
regarding this moment.

00:04:27.254 --> 00:04:30.076
And as we press on,

00:04:30.117 --> 00:04:33.399
it even appears that there is a direct

00:04:33.439 --> 00:04:36.762
correlation with the eighty-ninth Mizmowr,

00:04:36.783 --> 00:04:38.685
which is something I'll begin exploring

00:04:40.005 --> 00:04:40.887
later today.

00:04:41.848 --> 00:04:42.247
I have,

00:04:42.348 --> 00:04:43.970
so that you know where I stand in

00:04:44.110 --> 00:04:44.771
all of this,

00:04:46.675 --> 00:04:51.439
After we finish this review of Isaiah, fifty four

00:04:52.619 --> 00:04:57.161
that speaks of this remarkable woman and

00:04:57.721 --> 00:05:01.184
her role in building the covenant family.

00:05:04.005 --> 00:05:07.326
Because of Israel's bad behavior and their

00:05:08.028 --> 00:05:09.869
recalcitrance against Yahowah,

00:05:10.528 --> 00:05:13.670
erasing his name, rejecting his covenant.

00:05:14.894 --> 00:05:16.415
And failing to return to him,

00:05:16.875 --> 00:05:19.276
Israel has gone a little better part,

00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:19.677
excuse me,

00:05:19.697 --> 00:05:22.737
of three thousand years without adding

00:05:22.817 --> 00:05:24.298
anyone to the covenant family and

00:05:24.317 --> 00:05:26.939
therefore anyone into heaven.

00:05:27.819 --> 00:05:29.800
And so it is only during this time

00:05:29.819 --> 00:05:30.819
that there is an awakening,

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:34.221
a recognition of Yahowah's name,

00:05:34.362 --> 00:05:37.302
a realization that Dowd is the chosen one,

00:05:37.322 --> 00:05:38.543
the Messiah, the Messiah.

00:05:39.951 --> 00:05:40.512
son of God,

00:05:40.572 --> 00:05:43.656
and the one who fulfilled Pesach by being

00:05:43.697 --> 00:05:45.680
crucified in thirty-three CE,

00:05:45.839 --> 00:05:48.684
and who took our guilt into Sheowl on

00:05:48.704 --> 00:05:51.749
Matsah, also in thirty-three CE,

00:05:51.809 --> 00:05:53.250
to enable Bikuwrym,

00:05:53.271 --> 00:05:54.432
which is firstborn children.

00:05:55.694 --> 00:06:01.156
So as we came to that recognition,

00:06:01.677 --> 00:06:04.778
and we are pursuing that in here in

00:06:04.879 --> 00:06:06.178
Yashayah,

00:06:06.218 --> 00:06:08.180
which is a whole discussion about how

00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:10.461
she's going to become productive again,

00:06:11.480 --> 00:06:13.622
personalizing this through a single woman

00:06:13.682 --> 00:06:16.403
who plays the lead role in accomplishing

00:06:16.543 --> 00:06:18.204
this on behalf of Yisrael.

00:06:19.324 --> 00:06:21.584
From there, we are actually going to

00:06:22.877 --> 00:06:25.358
jump into what is the darkest episode

00:06:26.399 --> 00:06:27.899
anywhere in the Towrah,

00:06:27.959 --> 00:06:28.899
Prophets and Psalms.

00:06:28.980 --> 00:06:33.100
It is Second Shemuel, eleven and twelve.

00:06:34.002 --> 00:06:37.163
And I'm going to share with you what

00:06:37.223 --> 00:06:37.702
Dowd did.

00:06:38.702 --> 00:06:40.004
It was one of the hardest things I've

00:06:40.124 --> 00:06:40.603
ever written.

00:06:40.963 --> 00:06:42.103
I had thought at the time it would

00:06:42.124 --> 00:06:43.444
be the hardest thing I would ever have

00:06:43.485 --> 00:06:43.805
to do.

00:06:44.985 --> 00:06:46.925
But it's something that we knew we had

00:06:46.966 --> 00:06:52.208
to cover because in rabbinical lore,

00:06:54.211 --> 00:06:55.851
Dowd is disqualified as being the

00:06:55.891 --> 00:06:57.612
returning Messiah.

00:06:58.612 --> 00:07:00.973
He is disqualified as being a son of

00:07:01.033 --> 00:07:01.312
God.

00:07:01.372 --> 00:07:03.533
He is disqualified as being the returning

00:07:03.593 --> 00:07:06.774
King because of the malfeasance of this

00:07:07.014 --> 00:07:07.394
moment.

00:07:07.754 --> 00:07:08.894
And so we have to deal with it.

00:07:09.735 --> 00:07:10.995
And in Christianity,

00:07:11.574 --> 00:07:15.656
those who are somewhat thoughtful in

00:07:15.696 --> 00:07:18.456
trying to defend the lie and the mythology

00:07:18.656 --> 00:07:20.396
of their man, God, Jesus,

00:07:21.197 --> 00:07:24.259
say that there had to be some miracle

00:07:24.699 --> 00:07:30.841
birth and perfect person to fulfill this

00:07:30.901 --> 00:07:31.283
promise.

00:07:31.322 --> 00:07:32.682
They don't even know what the promise was.

00:07:32.702 --> 00:07:35.524
They have no concept that he fulfilled

00:07:35.624 --> 00:07:36.745
Passover and Matsah.

00:07:37.185 --> 00:07:38.725
But nonetheless, they want perfection.

00:07:39.533 --> 00:07:45.262
And because Dowd was so imperfect at this

00:07:45.482 --> 00:07:45.822
moment,

00:07:46.644 --> 00:07:48.927
he is automatically disqualified in their

00:07:48.966 --> 00:07:49.346
minds.

00:07:49.406 --> 00:07:50.889
And so it's something, again,

00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:53.293
that we need to deal with for exactly

00:07:54.213 --> 00:07:55.536
this same reason.

00:07:57.033 --> 00:07:57.213
Now,

00:07:57.774 --> 00:08:01.156
that brings us to the overall problem,

00:08:01.177 --> 00:08:02.678
and I'm looking over my shoulder.

00:08:02.738 --> 00:08:04.279
My wife likes to come and go,

00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:05.360
which she's welcome to do,

00:08:05.401 --> 00:08:07.682
but we have a second camera that actually

00:08:07.723 --> 00:08:08.684
catches that door,

00:08:08.723 --> 00:08:10.745
and we just as soon not have it

00:08:11.125 --> 00:08:11.706
left open.

00:08:13.588 --> 00:08:20.173
The fact is that there is a grotesque

00:08:20.233 --> 00:08:21.033
misperception.

00:08:22.192 --> 00:08:25.954
of what is presented in English

00:08:25.973 --> 00:08:27.413
translations is perfect.

00:08:27.454 --> 00:08:28.875
It Dowdsn't mean perfect at all.

00:08:28.915 --> 00:08:30.535
The word is tamym,

00:08:31.235 --> 00:08:34.596
and it actually is from the root tamam,

00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:37.057
and it means to finish the job.

00:08:37.456 --> 00:08:38.636
If you finish the job,

00:08:38.697 --> 00:08:40.878
then you are living up to the expectations

00:08:40.898 --> 00:08:41.638
that God has,

00:08:41.677 --> 00:08:43.859
and you're totally qualified to do really

00:08:43.879 --> 00:08:45.379
any mission that God wants done.

00:08:45.639 --> 00:08:47.700
He just wants people that will have some

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:48.440
resolve and

00:08:49.013 --> 00:08:51.195
and fortitude and are willing to see it

00:08:51.215 --> 00:08:51.615
through.

00:08:52.134 --> 00:08:53.496
And Dowd became that man.

00:08:53.956 --> 00:08:58.880
So Dowd earned our respect by actually

00:08:59.221 --> 00:09:01.001
coming to grips with who he was and

00:09:01.081 --> 00:09:03.543
what he represents and what he needed to

00:09:03.583 --> 00:09:06.025
accomplish in his second of three lives to

00:09:06.066 --> 00:09:07.707
fulfill Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym.

00:09:08.849 --> 00:09:09.469
And he did.

00:09:10.308 --> 00:09:13.549
And there is an enormous amount of proof

00:09:13.690 --> 00:09:14.429
in this regard.

00:09:14.450 --> 00:09:15.570
But we're going to go through his

00:09:15.629 --> 00:09:16.029
meltdown.

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:17.291
And then following that,

00:09:17.650 --> 00:09:19.150
I'm going to share with you the most

00:09:20.530 --> 00:09:22.751
horrible thing that I thought I'd ever

00:09:22.831 --> 00:09:23.111
see.

00:09:23.152 --> 00:09:26.131
Far worse than Dowd's malfeasance in that

00:09:26.172 --> 00:09:28.072
whole affair, which is quite graphic.

00:09:30.212 --> 00:09:36.173
Dowd is angry at God for leaving him.

00:09:37.523 --> 00:09:40.063
for blaming him, for pretending,

00:09:40.945 --> 00:09:42.004
from Dowd's point of view,

00:09:42.065 --> 00:09:44.447
that he was somehow worse than everybody

00:09:44.527 --> 00:09:44.787
else.

00:09:44.826 --> 00:09:45.667
From his point of view,

00:09:45.706 --> 00:09:46.768
everybody was terrible.

00:09:46.827 --> 00:09:49.129
So, you know, what he did,

00:09:49.308 --> 00:09:51.910
he didn't think deserved the kind of

00:09:52.091 --> 00:09:55.331
rebuke that he received from God.

00:09:56.113 --> 00:09:58.994
And he wrote the fifty-first Mashal,

00:09:59.455 --> 00:10:01.316
not Mashal, but Mizmowr, psalm,

00:10:02.596 --> 00:10:03.636
in a really bad mood.

00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:06.640
but I think it's important for you to

00:10:06.681 --> 00:10:10.522
know how far he fell.

00:10:10.542 --> 00:10:11.081
Following that,

00:10:11.101 --> 00:10:12.842
there was an amazing intervention,

00:10:12.883 --> 00:10:16.224
and I'm going to ultimately share the

00:10:16.303 --> 00:10:18.345
second part of the intervention because

00:10:19.166 --> 00:10:22.167
the meeting between Dowd and his surrogate

00:10:22.187 --> 00:10:24.908
mother, Leah, the Ashar,

00:10:26.928 --> 00:10:31.629
got his attention and earned his respect,

00:10:32.311 --> 00:10:32.951
sobered him up,

00:10:34.884 --> 00:10:37.927
But it was the subsequent meeting that

00:10:37.947 --> 00:10:39.808
made the biggest difference.

00:10:39.869 --> 00:10:41.009
And it was delivered by another

00:10:41.029 --> 00:10:41.530
individual.

00:10:41.551 --> 00:10:42.751
And then I'm going to share the text

00:10:42.792 --> 00:10:45.475
with that, which is a very familiar text.

00:10:45.514 --> 00:10:47.756
It's just that we didn't know who the

00:10:47.836 --> 00:10:51.520
delivery person was the last time we

00:10:51.581 --> 00:10:52.022
reviewed it.

00:10:52.562 --> 00:10:53.562
So we'll go through that.

00:10:54.124 --> 00:10:55.585
And I want to...

00:10:56.744 --> 00:11:00.687
leave on a really upbeat note uh in

00:11:00.726 --> 00:11:05.051
this whole uh process so we're going to

00:11:05.091 --> 00:11:07.452
cover the hundred and sixteenth Mizmowr

00:11:07.993 --> 00:11:11.996
which is a celebration of Dowd getting it

00:11:12.037 --> 00:11:15.479
right again of him not only recognizing

00:11:15.519 --> 00:11:16.740
who he is and what he needs to

00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:18.961
do but laying it all out and saying

00:11:19.042 --> 00:11:20.803
i'm happy to do it this is what

00:11:20.844 --> 00:11:22.345
i'm going to accomplish i am going to

00:11:22.384 --> 00:11:23.985
see it through and it's going to be

00:11:24.025 --> 00:11:24.466
glorious

00:11:26.962 --> 00:11:29.143
So we have quite the process here to

00:11:29.182 --> 00:11:29.663
go through.

00:11:31.344 --> 00:11:32.923
When we encounter something that is

00:11:33.024 --> 00:11:36.225
profound in terms of what it adds to

00:11:36.264 --> 00:11:38.044
our understanding of God's story,

00:11:39.105 --> 00:11:41.065
I don't like to tease.

00:11:41.525 --> 00:11:43.725
My view is if God's going to take

00:11:43.745 --> 00:11:45.865
the time to tell us something that's this

00:11:46.245 --> 00:11:48.326
insightful, this compelling,

00:11:48.907 --> 00:11:50.086
the least we can do is see it

00:11:50.126 --> 00:11:52.567
all the way through and understand all of

00:11:52.586 --> 00:11:53.447
the implications.

00:11:53.528 --> 00:11:55.347
And that's precisely what we're going to

00:11:55.388 --> 00:11:55.467
do.

00:11:55.947 --> 00:11:56.849
So I want to pick up the story

00:11:56.869 --> 00:11:58.730
where we were in our last program.

00:11:58.750 --> 00:12:02.134
This would have been on Friday evening.

00:12:03.556 --> 00:12:05.038
And it reads,

00:12:06.259 --> 00:12:08.081
during a brief moment of time.

00:12:08.120 --> 00:12:10.322
That's kind of funny.

00:12:10.703 --> 00:12:11.504
From God's point of view,

00:12:11.565 --> 00:12:12.164
I'm sure it was.

00:12:12.184 --> 00:12:13.046
It could have been the blink of an

00:12:13.206 --> 00:12:13.366
eye.

00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:14.307
Yeah.

00:12:17.379 --> 00:12:19.080
In reality, it was a very,

00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:21.100
very long time, thousands of years.

00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:24.761
But time Dowdsn't move the same for all

00:12:24.802 --> 00:12:25.121
of us,

00:12:25.221 --> 00:12:27.802
and the seventh dimension time is whatever

00:12:27.822 --> 00:12:28.663
you'd like it to be.

00:12:29.364 --> 00:12:31.504
So during a brief moment in time,

00:12:31.565 --> 00:12:32.965
it's ba rega',

00:12:33.605 --> 00:12:35.865
in a disturbing instant and for a little

00:12:35.905 --> 00:12:40.008
while, as trifling and unworthy,

00:12:40.788 --> 00:12:44.269
and Israel certainly had become that.

00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:46.331
God says, I left you.

00:12:47.032 --> 00:12:48.493
I rejected and I released you.

00:12:49.052 --> 00:12:51.254
It's important for us to understand

00:12:51.294 --> 00:12:56.738
because Jews have a tendency to think that

00:12:56.878 --> 00:12:58.219
God is still protecting them,

00:12:58.259 --> 00:12:59.879
that God is right there with them,

00:12:59.919 --> 00:13:03.501
that they can go to their western wall

00:13:03.581 --> 00:13:03.662
and

00:13:05.134 --> 00:13:06.674
bob their heads up and down and put

00:13:06.695 --> 00:13:08.495
a piece of paper between the cracks and

00:13:08.875 --> 00:13:11.495
God's listening to their prayers and that

00:13:11.515 --> 00:13:13.476
he is involved in their day-to-day lives

00:13:13.517 --> 00:13:15.097
and nothing can be further from the truth.

00:13:15.138 --> 00:13:16.177
God's very clear.

00:13:16.597 --> 00:13:17.578
I left you.

00:13:17.599 --> 00:13:19.058
I mean,

00:13:19.078 --> 00:13:22.260
Azab is not a word that anybody has

00:13:22.301 --> 00:13:24.861
