Unable to manage his affairs,

00:56:23.673 --> 00:56:26.094
Dowd's scheme flopped.

00:56:27.034 --> 00:56:30.416
He wanted this honorable soldier to have

00:56:30.476 --> 00:56:33.817
sex with his wife so that he could

00:56:33.836 --> 00:56:36.318
be lured into believing that the child was

00:56:36.358 --> 00:56:36.717
his.

00:56:37.559 --> 00:56:39.318
But as it would transpire,

00:56:40.199 --> 00:56:44.021
'Uwryah showed no interest in his home or

00:56:44.061 --> 00:56:44.541
his wife.

00:56:45.856 --> 00:56:47.436
And considering the evidence at our

00:56:47.476 --> 00:56:48.077
disposal,

00:56:48.177 --> 00:56:50.699
I think that he knew what we have

00:56:50.780 --> 00:56:51.340
surmised.

00:56:52.862 --> 00:56:53.862
She wasn't a prize,

00:56:54.922 --> 00:56:56.945
and he hadn't been the last man in

00:56:56.985 --> 00:57:00.947
his home or his bed.

00:57:01.007 --> 00:57:03.210
He had gone, had he gone home,

00:57:04.010 --> 00:57:05.632
I think that sparks would have flown,

00:57:06.773 --> 00:57:08.134
but not of the loving kind.

00:57:10.255 --> 00:57:10.936
Nevertheless,

00:57:11.157 --> 00:57:12.918
'Uwryah was an exceptional man.

00:57:13.378 --> 00:57:15.699
He was likely covenant.

00:57:16.420 --> 00:57:18.320
He exhibited exemplary character

00:57:18.360 --> 00:57:18.762
throughout.

00:57:19.702 --> 00:57:22.224
The lone stalwart in this whole story.

00:57:22.523 --> 00:57:23.364
There was only one.

00:57:24.385 --> 00:57:27.027
And after hearing his response,

00:57:27.067 --> 00:57:28.829
had Dowd been of sound mind,

00:57:29.688 --> 00:57:30.630
he would have broken down.

00:57:31.530 --> 00:57:32.150
He would have wept.

00:57:35.132 --> 00:57:36.833
This is what comes next.

00:57:38.746 --> 00:57:40.786
'Uwryah, the light of Yah, said to Dowd,

00:57:40.806 --> 00:57:44.769
the beloved, the ark, Yisrael,

00:57:45.710 --> 00:57:50.413
and Yahuwdah dwell in Sukkoth, shelters,

00:57:51.514 --> 00:57:53.795
along with my lord, Yow'ab,

00:57:54.516 --> 00:57:57.077
in addition to the servants of my lord,

00:57:57.858 --> 00:58:02.320
bivouacked under siege in the presence of

00:58:02.420 --> 00:58:05.282
open terrain.

00:58:05.322 --> 00:58:07.324
So am I myself,

00:58:08.501 --> 00:58:12.362
supposed to go to my home to eat,

00:58:12.882 --> 00:58:15.264
to drink, and to lay with my wife?

00:58:16.744 --> 00:58:19.324
As you live and as your soul lives,

00:58:19.726 --> 00:58:22.025
I will not act this way or do

00:58:22.065 --> 00:58:25.746
this thing.

00:58:25.806 --> 00:58:30.469
Second Samuel, eleven, eleven.

00:58:30.588 --> 00:58:32.128
Then Dowd said to 'Uwryah,

00:58:33.110 --> 00:58:34.369
stay here this day also,

00:58:34.449 --> 00:58:36.510
and tomorrow I'll send you back.

00:58:37.440 --> 00:58:40.423
So 'Uwryah remained in Jerusalem that day

00:58:40.543 --> 00:58:42.326
and through the following day.

00:58:42.385 --> 00:58:43.887
Can you imagine what he's thinking?

00:58:44.547 --> 00:58:46.429
He wants me to go home and sleep

00:58:46.449 --> 00:58:47.251
with my wife.

00:58:48.612 --> 00:58:49.833
I told him I wouldn't do it.

00:58:51.135 --> 00:58:51.835
And he says, well,

00:58:51.896 --> 00:58:52.856
I'm going to send you back.

00:58:54.277 --> 00:58:55.840
But stay another day with me,

00:58:55.880 --> 00:58:56.800
then I'll send you back.

00:58:57.637 --> 00:58:59.778
You think just maybe he's saying,

00:59:00.259 --> 00:59:02.820
I suspect something really odd is going on

00:59:02.860 --> 00:59:05.322
here since I'm not your top general,

00:59:05.362 --> 00:59:07.483
since I'm not a messenger reporting on the

00:59:07.523 --> 00:59:07.782
war,

00:59:08.523 --> 00:59:12.425
since you called me out of nowhere for

00:59:12.465 --> 00:59:14.106
this meeting and you haven't bothered to

00:59:14.126 --> 00:59:15.626
explain why you called it,

00:59:16.027 --> 00:59:17.668
why you wanted me to go to my

00:59:17.748 --> 00:59:21.048
wife and why you're now want me to

00:59:21.509 --> 00:59:24.190
come over as we see for dinner and

00:59:24.231 --> 00:59:24.670
drinks.

00:59:25.818 --> 00:59:27.159
even after I told you that I wouldn't

00:59:27.179 --> 00:59:30.661
do such a thing.

00:59:30.702 --> 00:59:30.882
I mean,

00:59:30.922 --> 00:59:35.184
this is really weird in a very bad

00:59:35.244 --> 00:59:38.668
sort of way.

00:59:38.688 --> 00:59:44.331
Dowd summoned him again and Dowd ate in

00:59:44.371 --> 00:59:49.454
his presence and he drank excessively so

00:59:49.474 --> 00:59:52.516
that he caused even the man himself to

00:59:52.556 --> 00:59:52.916
be drunk.

00:59:54.057 --> 00:59:54.659
And he went out

00:59:55.498 --> 00:59:59.199
in the early evening to lay down on

00:59:59.239 --> 01:00:01.800
his bed with the servants of his Lord,

01:00:02.762 --> 01:00:06.523
but to his house he did not descend.

01:00:09.806 --> 01:00:10.146
Wow,

01:00:11.626 --> 01:00:13.748
this was a contrast between good and bad

01:00:13.788 --> 01:00:14.947
for sure, right and wrong.

01:00:15.509 --> 01:00:16.608
And our King was on the right,

01:00:16.809 --> 01:00:18.250
wrong side of this.

01:00:18.889 --> 01:00:20.990
After a man named Light of Yah stood

01:00:21.090 --> 01:00:23.393
up for the covenant for Yisrael,

01:00:24.621 --> 01:00:25.402
For the king,

01:00:25.621 --> 01:00:27.943
foregoing the comforts of home by

01:00:28.623 --> 01:00:31.686
respecting that his comrades were out in

01:00:31.726 --> 01:00:34.726
the elements away from home and exposed to

01:00:34.746 --> 01:00:35.288
the enemy,

01:00:36.047 --> 01:00:40.331
Dowd flaunted his situation by eating and

01:00:40.451 --> 01:00:43.813
drinking to excess.

01:00:43.833 --> 01:00:44.552
Can you imagine?

01:00:47.135 --> 01:00:47.335
I mean,

01:00:47.375 --> 01:00:51.637
Dowd's response was both callous and

01:00:51.697 --> 01:00:52.137
hedonistic.

01:00:54.076 --> 01:00:56.496
He was the furthest thing from an exemplar

01:00:56.538 --> 01:00:57.177
at this moment.

01:00:57.237 --> 01:00:57.918
And in fact,

01:00:58.458 --> 01:01:01.280
he was validating all of my prior

01:01:01.521 --> 01:01:04.382
conclusions that he had been drinking to

01:01:04.442 --> 01:01:08.043
excess and he did so to deaden his

01:01:08.105 --> 01:01:10.905
conscience to what he had become.

01:01:13.507 --> 01:01:14.809
But of course that wasn't the worst of

01:01:14.849 --> 01:01:18.731
it, not by a long shot.

01:01:23.469 --> 01:01:27.490
It transpired in the morning.

01:01:27.550 --> 01:01:27.710
God,

01:01:27.771 --> 01:01:36.413
I hate to read this letter to you.

01:01:36.432 --> 01:01:37.092
Dowd wrote a letter.

01:01:39.793 --> 01:01:42.454
It was written to Yow'ab.

01:01:45.134 --> 01:01:49.094
It was sent by the hand of 'Uwryah.

01:01:54.030 --> 01:01:54.550
In the letter,

01:01:56.632 --> 01:02:02.614
he wrote so as to say,

01:02:02.715 --> 01:02:08.898
it is imperative that you, Yow'ab,

01:02:11.159 --> 01:02:15.742
ascribe to and permit this.

01:02:15.782 --> 01:02:18.943
Placing 'Uwryah, Mul,

01:02:21.052 --> 01:02:28.556
cut off as if a removed foreskin.

01:02:28.597 --> 01:02:30.759
In direct proximity to the fiercest and

01:02:30.818 --> 01:02:31.579
most severe,

01:02:32.619 --> 01:02:34.742
the most obstinate combatants in the

01:02:34.762 --> 01:02:37.204
battle.

01:02:37.224 --> 01:02:38.324
Then retreat from him,

01:02:39.726 --> 01:02:42.186
turning on him from behind his back,

01:02:44.628 --> 01:02:46.130
so that he will be struck down and

01:02:46.170 --> 01:02:48.652
wounded, then die.

01:02:53.074 --> 01:02:55.596
Samuel, listen to God.

01:02:55.615 --> 01:03:09.440
Two Samuel, eleven, fifteen.

01:03:09.460 --> 01:03:13.523
You probably noted that I shared the

01:03:13.563 --> 01:03:17.864
Hebrew origin of the text that was

01:03:17.923 --> 01:03:19.465
underlying this written letter.

01:03:22.050 --> 01:03:25.373
including both Yahab and Mo.

01:03:27.735 --> 01:03:29.556
And I did so because I wanted you

01:03:29.597 --> 01:03:32.420
to know that I'm accurately reporting the

01:03:32.460 --> 01:03:33.179
bad news.

01:03:35.663 --> 01:03:38.324
Dowd wanted 'Uwryah, the light of Yah,

01:03:39.766 --> 01:03:44.769
snuffed out and tossed away like one of

01:03:44.809 --> 01:03:47.952
the two hundred Philistine foreskins he

01:03:48.072 --> 01:03:50.375
used to acquire Michel from Sha'uwl.

01:03:53.382 --> 01:03:55.902
And he was insistent that Yow'ab,

01:03:55.963 --> 01:03:56.882
father of Yahowah,

01:03:58.063 --> 01:04:02.565
bend his will to his own and not

01:04:02.664 --> 01:04:04.666
only permit this atrocity,

01:04:05.346 --> 01:04:06.786
but participate in it,

01:04:08.166 --> 01:04:15.190
making Yow'ab an accessory to murder.

01:04:15.230 --> 01:04:20.211
Makes my stomach turn, my head throb.

01:04:20.311 --> 01:04:20.992
It's heartbreaking.

01:04:25.478 --> 01:04:28.219
So it came to be as Yow'ab was

01:04:28.280 --> 01:04:30.101
observing, closely examining,

01:04:30.141 --> 01:04:32.443
and carefully considering the approach to

01:04:32.523 --> 01:04:38.007
the city, he assigned 'Uwryah,

01:04:38.608 --> 01:04:39.349
the light of Yah,

01:04:40.751 --> 01:04:42.431
to the place where he knew that the

01:04:42.472 --> 01:04:44.914
most physically strong and vigorous men

01:04:44.994 --> 01:04:48.996
would be there.

01:04:49.016 --> 01:04:51.579
When the men came out of the city

01:04:51.639 --> 01:04:53.400
and fought against Yow'ab,

01:04:54.889 --> 01:04:56.851
and some of the people among the servants

01:04:56.911 --> 01:04:57.751
of Dowd fell.

01:04:59.771 --> 01:05:04.293
Then 'Uwryah the Chitti, he also died.

01:05:07.655 --> 01:05:09.416
Second Samuel, eleven, seventeen.

01:05:12.117 --> 01:05:16.639
Many men were deliberately sacrificed and

01:05:16.699 --> 01:05:17.059
died,

01:05:18.418 --> 01:05:21.440
including one who was essentially

01:05:21.460 --> 01:05:22.201
assassinated.

01:05:23.907 --> 01:05:27.048
so that a cowardly, self-indulgent,

01:05:28.349 --> 01:05:32.150
debauched drunkard could add another man's

01:05:32.250 --> 01:05:33.349
wife to his harem.

01:05:36.530 --> 01:05:40.010
The crown of Yisrael had clearly lost its

01:05:40.070 --> 01:05:40.550
luster.

01:05:42.192 --> 01:05:47.012
A once good man had fallen and no

01:05:47.052 --> 01:05:50.172
longer had the capacity, moral fortitude,

01:05:51.673 --> 01:05:52.934
or resolve to get back up.

01:05:56.072 --> 01:05:58.474
Now in his defense, he had been exemplary,

01:05:59.114 --> 01:05:59.835
even brilliant.

01:06:01.235 --> 01:06:05.079
From eight years old to fifty-six years of

01:06:05.179 --> 01:06:05.440
age,

01:06:06.740 --> 01:06:09.603
he was one of the most heroic characters

01:06:09.663 --> 01:06:13.425
for forty-eight years before squandering

01:06:13.465 --> 01:06:17.248
the most burnished of all human resumes.

01:06:17.268 --> 01:06:23.054
Let's put this in perspective.

01:06:24.409 --> 01:06:25.668
Abraham, by contrast,

01:06:26.369 --> 01:06:29.449
was really never brilliant and all too

01:06:29.510 --> 01:06:31.170
often ignoble.

01:06:32.050 --> 01:06:35.251
The same can be said of Yitschaq, Jacob,

01:06:35.451 --> 01:06:36.231
and Esau,

01:06:36.911 --> 01:06:38.911
and even of the twelve sons of Yisrael.

01:06:39.431 --> 01:06:42.231
Moshe didn't last a year before he begged

01:06:42.291 --> 01:06:43.032
God to kill him.

01:06:45.333 --> 01:06:49.693
So Dowd had set an endurance record of

01:06:49.753 --> 01:06:53.693
forty-eight years in the spotlight.

01:06:55.239 --> 01:06:59.782
before jumping out of it.

01:06:59.882 --> 01:07:04.344
At twenty-four years under that same

01:07:04.405 --> 01:07:04.985
scrutiny,

01:07:05.085 --> 01:07:07.547
which is all that I have invested,

01:07:08.047 --> 01:07:08.248
you know,

01:07:08.268 --> 01:07:11.510
I have empathy for the difficulty of the

01:07:11.889 --> 01:07:12.971
situation he was in.

01:07:13.972 --> 01:07:17.273
I'm only halfway to what Dowd managed to

01:07:17.333 --> 01:07:18.954
achieve in terms of longevity.

01:07:20.139 --> 01:07:24.443
And perhaps it is this unique perspective

01:07:24.483 --> 01:07:26.525
that gives me the ability to push through

01:07:26.585 --> 01:07:30.188
this darkness and to reestablish the light

01:07:30.228 --> 01:07:32.891
which had once shown so brightly,

01:07:34.311 --> 01:07:35.813
especially knowing that the fate of the

01:07:35.853 --> 01:07:39.396
world rests on rekindling it and then

01:07:39.456 --> 01:07:42.739
reestablishing it.

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:45.782
Yahowah was, as we shall soon see,

01:07:47.960 --> 01:07:49.940
badly hurt.

01:07:50.061 --> 01:07:51.402
He's extremely disappointed.

01:07:52.541 --> 01:07:53.302
But deep down,

01:07:53.362 --> 01:07:55.802
God also knew that he had tried and

01:07:55.862 --> 01:07:58.043
failed when representing himself.

01:07:59.422 --> 01:08:02.503
He had grown resentful, then vengeful,

01:08:02.684 --> 01:08:05.583
and would even withdraw.

01:08:05.963 --> 01:08:07.465
He would allow his people to suffer

01:08:07.585 --> 01:08:09.684
unimaginable heartache and abuse,

01:08:10.344 --> 01:08:14.085
and he would cause even many to die.

01:08:16.307 --> 01:08:18.630
And so while Yahowah's indignation was

01:08:18.689 --> 01:08:19.210
righteous,

01:08:20.270 --> 01:08:23.172
and while he never compromised on his

01:08:23.393 --> 01:08:28.176
moral integrity, in some ways, like son,

01:08:28.216 --> 01:08:32.158
like father, both tried hard,

01:08:32.279 --> 01:08:34.520
were virtuous, and then, well,

01:08:34.560 --> 01:08:37.421
gave up after a long while.

01:08:38.662 --> 01:08:39.884
God remained virtuous,

01:08:39.923 --> 01:08:41.225
but he certainly gave up.

01:08:44.167 --> 01:08:49.631
So this is what makes the job that

01:08:49.690 --> 01:08:52.231
Leigh and I are trying to accomplish and

01:08:52.311 --> 01:08:56.175
will fulfill all the more remarkable and

01:08:56.215 --> 01:08:56.654
compelling.

01:08:58.796 --> 01:09:01.837
It is why there are no or there

01:09:01.877 --> 01:09:04.159
are upwards of, I guess,

01:09:04.779 --> 01:09:06.862
well over a thousand prophetic references

01:09:06.902 --> 01:09:10.764
now that we're examining them regarding

01:09:10.884 --> 01:09:11.904
this specific mission.

01:09:13.293 --> 01:09:14.435
and likely so many more.

01:09:16.074 --> 01:09:16.315
I mean,

01:09:16.336 --> 01:09:18.197
it's the essence of the last Mashal.

01:09:20.177 --> 01:09:21.957
It will be the subject of the greatest

01:09:22.719 --> 01:09:27.280
of all songs.

01:09:27.320 --> 01:09:30.162
So moving on with the story of Dowd's

01:09:30.523 --> 01:09:32.003
midlife crisis, we read,

01:09:33.363 --> 01:09:36.326
then Yahowah sent a dispatch to tell Dowd

01:09:40.028 --> 01:09:42.128
all of the matters related to the war.

01:09:44.217 --> 01:09:51.202
Yow'ab is telling Dowd what happened.

01:09:53.423 --> 01:09:54.663
And he instructed the Malak,

01:09:54.704 --> 01:09:55.465
this messenger,

01:09:55.524 --> 01:09:57.645
saying that when you have finished the

01:09:57.706 --> 01:10:00.627
entire report pertaining to this battle

01:10:00.707 --> 01:10:02.989
and this war,

01:10:03.869 --> 01:10:05.171
while you're speaking to the king,

01:10:06.851 --> 01:10:08.693
if it comes to be that the king's

01:10:09.314 --> 01:10:09.774
Chima,

01:10:10.274 --> 01:10:13.115
venomous fury and toxic rage

01:10:14.556 --> 01:10:17.797
rises, escalating before you.

01:10:19.297 --> 01:10:20.378
And he says to you,

01:10:21.759 --> 01:10:24.520
on whose account did you approach the city

01:10:24.560 --> 01:10:25.159
to fight?

01:10:25.940 --> 01:10:28.661
Why were you unaware that they would shoot

01:10:28.841 --> 01:10:30.362
arrows from the wall?

01:10:31.021 --> 01:10:35.023
Who struck Amalek, my father is king,

01:10:35.063 --> 01:10:37.923
the son of Yerbusheth,

01:10:38.404 --> 01:10:39.744
I strive to confuse.

01:10:40.713 --> 01:10:42.835
Was there not a woman to cast upon

01:10:42.875 --> 01:10:46.237
him a chariot mount and millstone from the

01:10:46.277 --> 01:10:49.658
wall so that he was killed in or

01:10:49.738 --> 01:10:54.721
with Tebets conspicuous?

01:10:54.762 --> 01:10:59.364
So why did you approach the wall?

01:10:59.465 --> 01:11:03.148
Then you have told the messenger,

01:11:03.328 --> 01:11:09.591
you should say, your servant, 'Uwryah,

01:11:09.631 --> 01:11:10.231
the light of Yah,

01:11:11.208 --> 01:11:14.310
The Chity fearsome is dead.

01:11:21.356 --> 01:11:24.059
So the Malak messenger walked and came to

01:11:24.118 --> 01:11:27.221
Dowd and reported everything that Yow'ab

01:11:27.261 --> 01:11:30.444
had dispatched him to tell.

01:11:30.484 --> 01:11:34.046
Second Samuel, eleven twenty two.

01:11:34.087 --> 01:11:34.207
Now,

01:11:34.226 --> 01:11:36.969
we can only assume that this Malak

01:11:37.009 --> 01:11:37.470
messenger

01:11:38.720 --> 01:11:42.341
concocted the following pretext to the

01:11:42.582 --> 01:11:48.463
ensuing battle, to avoid the king's wrath,

01:11:48.484 --> 01:11:51.324
because it is clearly inconsistent with

01:11:52.505 --> 01:11:54.286
Dowd's prior instructions,

01:11:55.086 --> 01:11:59.188
as well as Yow'ab's preceding observations.

01:12:01.243 --> 01:12:03.145
So the Moloch messenger said to Dowd,

01:12:03.185 --> 01:12:04.485
surely the Gabar,

01:12:04.506 --> 01:12:07.368
the strongest and most overbearing men

01:12:07.427 --> 01:12:10.270
triumphed over us as individual men.

01:12:10.871 --> 01:12:13.393
They came out against us upon the open

01:12:13.412 --> 01:12:13.832
field,

01:12:14.453 --> 01:12:17.695
but it came to be that we came

01:12:17.756 --> 01:12:20.939
upon them up to the opening of the

01:12:20.979 --> 01:12:22.399
gate.

01:12:22.720 --> 01:12:25.382
Then those casting arrows at your servants

01:12:25.422 --> 01:12:29.024
from upon the wall and some of the

01:12:29.045 --> 01:12:30.667
king's servants were slain.

01:12:31.966 --> 01:12:34.627
In addition, your servant, 'Uwryah,

01:12:34.686 --> 01:12:42.470
the light of Yah, the Chity, is dead.

01:12:42.529 --> 01:12:47.372
No grief, no remorse.

01:12:47.671 --> 01:12:50.733
The tirade of toxic vitriol was avoided by

01:12:50.813 --> 01:12:53.894
changing the story to absolve Yow'ab of

01:12:53.953 --> 01:12:58.475
complicity and Dowd of guilt in the

01:12:58.636 --> 01:13:01.037
successful assassination of a good man.

01:13:02.810 --> 01:13:08.353
thereby engulfing the light of Yah.

01:13:08.372 --> 01:13:08.632
Dowd,

01:13:08.672 --> 01:13:11.333
realizing that he had now committed murder

01:13:12.675 --> 01:13:15.916
and that Yow'ab could implicate him in

01:13:16.076 --> 01:13:18.817
treason,

01:13:18.837 --> 01:13:25.000
tried to assuage his general's conscience.

01:13:25.020 --> 01:13:26.220
Dowd said to the messenger,

01:13:26.740 --> 01:13:28.862
this is what you should say to Yow'ab.

01:13:31.515 --> 01:13:33.136
There is al-ra'ah,

01:13:33.497 --> 01:13:37.920
nothing evil or harmful, wrong or bad.

01:13:38.881 --> 01:13:41.922
In your eyes are perceptions with regard

01:13:41.962 --> 01:13:45.564
to this matter and these communications.

01:13:46.345 --> 01:13:49.347
Remember the choice of verb, ra'ah.

01:13:49.368 --> 01:13:52.569
Yahowah will use it.

01:13:52.609 --> 01:13:57.132
For indeed, as it is for one,

01:13:58.434 --> 01:14:00.375
so it is now likewise for the other.

01:14:02.210 --> 01:14:05.934
The sword of desolation consumes and

01:14:05.974 --> 01:14:08.476
devours.

01:14:08.697 --> 01:14:09.978
Oh, Dowd is saying,

01:14:09.997 --> 01:14:12.121
because you were complicit in my scheme,

01:14:12.201 --> 01:14:13.841
even though I ordered you to do so,

01:14:14.823 --> 01:14:18.167
now you were complicit in it and also

01:14:18.207 --> 01:14:19.207
guilty of murder.

01:14:19.649 --> 01:14:20.770
You keep that in mind.

01:14:23.680 --> 01:14:25.440
Be particularly harsh, Dowd said,

01:14:25.942 --> 01:14:26.542
and severe.

01:14:27.103 --> 01:14:30.005
Be relentless and resolved in your attack

01:14:30.685 --> 01:14:34.649
in this war against the city and tear

01:14:34.689 --> 01:14:36.831
it down, demolishing it,

01:14:37.551 --> 01:14:43.657
leaving it in ruins.

01:14:43.697 --> 01:14:45.417
Cities are filled with civilians,

01:14:45.698 --> 01:14:46.378
women and children.

01:14:49.073 --> 01:14:52.074
Thereby you must reinforce his intensity

01:14:52.154 --> 01:15:02.420
and resolve, toughening him up, God said.

01:15:02.439 --> 01:15:02.579
Well,

01:15:02.640 --> 01:15:04.220
I can tell you that was to Samuel,

01:15:04.520 --> 01:15:07.862
and as I read through this,

01:15:07.962 --> 01:15:11.484
I am grateful that Yahowah waited to this

01:15:11.524 --> 01:15:11.844
time,

01:15:11.923 --> 01:15:14.046
twenty-four years into our mission

01:15:14.086 --> 01:15:14.485
together.

01:15:17.421 --> 01:15:23.025
and that he waited to lead me to

01:15:23.105 --> 01:15:27.609
this result after having analyzed that

01:15:27.649 --> 01:15:28.590
final word picture,

01:15:29.770 --> 01:15:32.212
knowing that it was resolved.

01:15:34.774 --> 01:15:35.154
Or else,

01:15:35.895 --> 01:15:39.337
had I known how this travesty was

01:15:39.458 --> 01:15:40.559
ultimately resolved,

01:15:41.159 --> 01:15:43.261
I don't think I could have recovered

01:15:43.301 --> 01:15:43.862
sufficiently.

01:15:45.421 --> 01:15:47.542
from this to devote all of my energies

01:15:47.582 --> 01:15:50.862
to reestablishing the King's reputation to

01:15:50.902 --> 01:15:51.903
his former glory.

01:15:53.523 --> 01:15:55.264
But I know now how it was restored.

01:15:56.043 --> 01:15:57.583
I know the role that we played in

01:15:57.623 --> 01:16:00.024
that regard.

01:16:00.104 --> 01:16:04.265
And I know that it was completely

01:16:04.685 --> 01:16:05.145
restored.

01:16:06.207 --> 01:16:07.726
And now I, for the first time,

01:16:07.766 --> 01:16:10.768
having returned to the story in the

01:16:10.807 --> 01:16:11.127
garden,

01:16:13.095 --> 01:16:16.275
I realize that God has no concern over

01:16:17.676 --> 01:16:19.457
us making a mistake, even horrific,

01:16:21.057 --> 01:16:25.239
if we can prove ourselves trustworthy and

01:16:25.279 --> 01:16:26.060
finish the job.

01:16:29.442 --> 01:16:33.262
But ultimately, Dowd, he was just a man.

01:16:34.264 --> 01:16:35.224
Just like the rest of us.

01:16:37.005 --> 01:16:39.826
One put in a very difficult situation.

01:16:41.328 --> 01:16:45.292
He succeeded from eight to fifty six.

01:16:45.532 --> 01:16:46.693
That's forty eight years.

01:16:48.434 --> 01:16:50.716
Before spending the last fourteen or some

01:16:50.775 --> 01:16:52.778
portion of them embarrassed and isolated.

01:16:55.100 --> 01:16:58.162
Slicing himself down from exceptional to

01:16:58.243 --> 01:16:58.722
ordinary.

01:17:00.444 --> 01:17:02.787
With the sword of his own tongue.

01:17:05.739 --> 01:17:06.340
Ultimately,

01:17:06.420 --> 01:17:09.242
he would be inspired to fulfill Pesach,

01:17:09.301 --> 01:17:10.103
Matsah and Bikuwrym,

01:17:10.622 --> 01:17:12.904
more than making up for lost time and

01:17:12.963 --> 01:17:13.425
lives.

01:17:14.585 --> 01:17:18.207
But someone else would have to be brought

01:17:18.368 --> 01:17:22.609
into him for him to finish the job.

01:17:24.851 --> 01:17:26.613
He, like Moshe before him,

01:17:26.693 --> 01:17:28.673
couldn't complete it without intervention.

01:17:30.835 --> 01:17:33.377
It's hard to imagine, indeed, Stomach,

01:17:34.465 --> 01:17:35.805
that the man I've come to know and

01:17:35.845 --> 01:17:37.206
admire through his

01:17:37.246 --> 01:17:39.507
Mizmowr and Mashal as well as through the

01:17:39.667 --> 01:17:45.751
eyes of his father who loved him fell

01:17:45.791 --> 01:17:52.833
this precipitously.

01:17:52.854 --> 01:17:56.355
Dowd was telling the man who obviously

01:17:56.395 --> 01:17:58.716
knew better that there was nothing wrong

01:17:58.756 --> 01:18:01.359
with setting men up to die for his

01:18:01.399 --> 01:18:01.939
indulgence.

01:18:03.543 --> 01:18:06.324
The most heinous and appalling episode in

01:18:06.385 --> 01:18:09.386
his life wasn't to be perceived as evil,

01:18:09.926 --> 01:18:12.206
as raw, much less even wrong.

01:18:13.207 --> 01:18:13.907
Or else, of course,

01:18:13.926 --> 01:18:15.806
the people would turn on the king and

01:18:15.827 --> 01:18:17.368
do to him what he has done to

01:18:17.408 --> 01:18:19.007
the light of Yah.

01:18:19.287 --> 01:18:21.548
And in those words,

01:18:21.788 --> 01:18:23.229
at least for a time,

01:18:23.288 --> 01:18:25.670
the greater luminary ceased to shine.

01:18:27.670 --> 01:18:29.850
Flame had gone dark.

01:18:32.841 --> 01:18:34.743
Dowd was, of course,

01:18:35.743 --> 01:18:36.966
blackmailing his general.

01:18:38.506 --> 01:18:40.368
He said that the sword of conscience and

01:18:40.429 --> 01:18:42.431
confession would cut both ways,

01:18:43.393 --> 01:18:46.536
devouring the king and his executioner.

01:18:48.078 --> 01:18:49.099
They were in this together.

01:18:50.279 --> 01:18:51.921
Both compromised.

01:18:53.697 --> 01:18:54.818
Then for bad measure,

01:18:54.877 --> 01:18:57.020
the man who was lounging around,

01:18:57.159 --> 01:18:59.502
drinking to excess, sleeping around,

01:18:59.842 --> 01:19:02.725
said to the man wielding his sword that

01:19:02.784 --> 01:19:06.529
he should man up, intensify his resolve,

01:19:06.908 --> 01:19:08.850
be fierce in his demeanor.

01:19:10.072 --> 01:19:12.274
He was to rule through terror,

01:19:14.036 --> 01:19:17.439
tearing down and demolishing the city,

01:19:17.498 --> 01:19:18.439
leaving it in ruins.

01:19:22.109 --> 01:19:27.371
The most Yahuwd of men had become a

01:19:28.490 --> 01:19:29.470
run of the mill Goy.

01:19:32.311 --> 01:19:35.512
He was what Yahowah had told his people

01:19:35.573 --> 01:19:36.092
to avoid.

01:19:37.953 --> 01:19:41.234
And so it would take a Goy acting

01:19:41.274 --> 01:19:46.194
like a Yahuwd to save the savior of

01:19:46.274 --> 01:19:49.454
Israel and the planet,

01:19:49.576 --> 01:19:51.815
along with a very able assist.

01:19:53.439 --> 01:20:00.725
from a woman, his wife.

01:20:00.746 --> 01:20:03.207
There's more to the story and we will

01:20:03.247 --> 01:20:05.829
share it in the next episode of the

01:20:05.869 --> 01:20:06.530
Yahowah blog.

01:20:07.771 --> 01:20:09.373
I thank you for listening to the most

01:20:09.413 --> 01:20:11.416
painful presentation we have made thus

01:20:11.475 --> 01:20:11.815
far,

01:20:12.737 --> 01:20:14.597
although it will not be the most painful

01:20:14.637 --> 01:20:17.240
of all because that is next.